  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package is generated at Model Risk Level 3 to reflect an elevated regulatory scrutiny tier. All 13 ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 factors are addressed; however, the 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that the factor narrative argues it does not apply because test conditions were derived directly from predicate device specifications. The factor is not encoded as 'not-applicable', which would be the correct encoding if non-applicability had been formally demonstrated. At MRL 3 this unassessed factor materially weakens the overall credibility package.",
