    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the CFD hemolysis model for the CPB COU based on satisfactory performance across 12 of 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. All assessed factors achieved their required gradation levels at MRL 3. The 'Equivalency of input parameters' factor was not formally assessed; the team's narrative rationale argued non-applicability, but this was not encoded as 'not-applicable' per protocol. The decision to accept was made on the basis of the strong quantitative validation evidence (mean NIH error 8.3%, GCI 4.2%) and the direct derivation of boundary conditions from predicate device specifications. The unassessed factor represents a documentation gap that the team considered low-risk given the direct traceability of inputs.",
